Durban - Joint operations between the Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa (Prasa), Yellowwood Park Sector Policing Forum, and the community have been involved in the arrest of 98 suspects in the last 2.5 years, for theft or damage to critical infrastructure on the railway tracks. Jacques Stephens, an active community member, who has assisted in many different roles, made the revelation when providing a feedback report. He said he had received the feedback on Tuesday night, regarding convictions on the arrests. Here is a breakdown of their court appearances: “There are a lot of cases scheduled for the month of July and I will post a more detailed conviction breakdown at the end of July,” added Stephens. Daily News